FuncDef: This command configures the Dot1q Ethertype on the PW-port. The PW-port is used to extract a customer's Ethernet traffic that is transported in a tunnel over an IP/MPLS network. TheDot1q-etyperepresents the first two bytes (TPID) in the 802.1Q header of a single-tagged Ethernet frame or the inner 802.1Q header of the double-tagged Ethernet frame inside the tunnel.

ParaDef.Info: The value for the dot1q-etype field, in hexadecimal format. Values-0x0600..0xFFFF. ParamDefault: Default- 0x8100
